oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Walkway and well at Blount Mansion
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Rear view of the Blount Mansion, showing brick walkway and well. The walkway surrounds a tree. A piece of equipment is also in the yard and the back of the house is visible.
Blount mansion was the home of Governor of the Southwest Territory, William Blount. It served as the Capitol of the Southwest Territory.
